               <msContents>
                  <summary>Apollonios, not the dioiketes, informs Zenon that he has been approached by a would-be purchaser of the big horse, but he cannot bargain about the price unless he hears from Zenon how much he is asking for it.  He begs him to send his answer to Kerke.</summary>
